"{\"uid\": \"koaa.com-news-covering-colorado-2024-paris-olympic-medal-tracker\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The Paris Olympics have officially kicked off!\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 46, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4, \"end\": 18, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You can keep up with all of your Olympics content here on KOAA-TV.\", \"from\": 47, \"to\": 113, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 105, \"end\": 112, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/KOAA-TV\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"KOAA-TV\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/KOAA-TV\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/KOAA-TV\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team USA was off to a strong start to the games for the first weekend, bringing in 12 medals throughout the opening weekend of the games.\", \"from\": 115, \"to\": 252, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 115, \"end\": 123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.634659962223853e-23, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those medals all have ties to Olympic City USA as according to the city those medals were won by athletes who have worked and trained in Olympic City USA.\", \"from\": 254, \"to\": 408, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 404, \"end\": 407, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999308784, \"rank\": 6.941994820684593e-11, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Below you can see which sports Team USA has won medals in and which athletes competed to bring the medals home.\", \"from\": 412, \"to\": 523, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 443, \"end\": 451, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.634659962223853e-23, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So far, Team USA has dominated in swimming bringing home 28 medals.\", \"from\": 525, \"to\": 592, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 533, \"end\": 541, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.634659962223853e-23, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Of these, eight are gold, 13 are silver, and seven are bronze.\", \"from\": 593, \"to\": 655, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Katie Ledecky - Women's 800M Freestyle  Bobby Finke - Gold, Men's 1500M Freestyle  Katie Ledecky - Gold, Women's 1500M Freestyle  Kate Douglass - Gold, Women's 200M Breaststroke  Torri Huske - Gold, Women's 100 M Butterfly  Jack Alexy, Chris Guiliano, Hunter Armstrong, and Caeleb Dressel - Gold, Men's 4X100M Freestyle Relay  Regan Smith, Lilly King, Gretchen Walsh and Torri Huske - Gold, Women's 4X100 Medley Relay  Ryan Murphy, Gretchen Walsh, Nic Fink, and Torri Huske - Gold, Mixed 4X100 Medley Relay  Torri Huske - Silver, Women's 100M Freestyle  Bobby Finke - Silver, Men's 800M Freestyle  Regan Smith - Silver, Women's 100M Backstroke  Regan Smith - Silver, Women's 200M Backstroke  Nic Fink - Silver,  Men's 100M Breastroke  Gretchen Walsh - Silver,  Women's 100M Butterfly  Regan Smith - Silver, Women's 200M Butterfly  Kate Douglass - Silver, Women's 200M IM  Katie Grimes - Silver,  Women's 400M IM  Simone Manuel, Kate Douglass, Gretchen Walsh, and Torri Huske - Silver, Women's 4X100M Freestyle Relay  Luke Hobson, Carson Foster, Drew Kibler and Kieran Smith - Silver, Men's 4X200M Freestyle Relay  Katie Ledecky, Paige Madden, Claire Weinstein and Erin Gemmell - Silver, Women's 4X200M Freestyle Relay  Ryan Murphy, Nic Fink, Caeleb Dressel and Hunter Armstrong - Silver, Men's 4X100M Medley Relay  Luke Hobson - Bronze, Men's 200M Freestyle  Katie Ledecky - Bronze,  Women's 400M Freestyle  Paige Madden - Bronze, Women's 800M Freestyle  Ryan Murphy - Bronze, Men's 100M Backstroke  Katharine Berkoff - Bronze, Women's 100M Backstroke  Carson Foster - Bronze, Men's 400M IM  Emma Weyant - Bronze, Women's 400M IM  The fencing competition led to an interesting final in the women's individual foil as it was Team USA's Lauren Scruggs up against Team USA's Lee Kiefer.\", \"from\": 657, \"to\": 2440, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 657, \"end\": 670, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}, {\"begin\": 697, \"end\": 708, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Finke\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bobby Finke\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Finke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Finke\"}, {\"begin\": 740, \"end\": 753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/K